text: Kenneth Tencio Esquivel (born December 6, 1993) is a Costa Rican freestyle or freestyle BMX cyclist. He is an athlete known in Costa Rica for participating in freestyle BMX competitions in the X-Knights, winning a plata medal at the 2018 World Cycling World Championship and qualifying for the 2020 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:Living people Category:1993 births Category:Cyclists Category:Costa Rican sportspeople Category:Competitors at the 2020 Summer Olympics
